SIMPLE: wantonness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wantonness
<hw>Wan"ton*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
wanton; negligence of restraint; sportiveness; recklessness;
lasciviousness.</def> <rj><au>Gower.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The tumults threatened to abuse all acts of grace, and turn them
into <qex>wantonness</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Eikon Basilike.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Young gentlemen would be as sad as night⟦br⟧
Only for <qex>wantonness</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wantrust</ent>⟦br⟧
